ðŸš€ VoiceUP Backend - Setup Guide

This guide will help you set up the backend environment for the VoiceUP academic project.

1. Prerequisites

Python 3.8+ installed.

PostgreSQL installed and running.

2. Installation

First, install all the necessary Python libraries globally (as agreed for this prototype):

pip install -r requirements.txt


3. Database Configuration

Open pgAdmin 4 or your terminal.

Create a new database named voiceup_db.

Create a file named .env in the root folder of the project and paste the following (replace with your PostgreSQL password):

DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:YOUR_PASSWORD@localhost:5432/voiceup_db
UPLOAD_FOLDER=uploads


4. First Run & Data Seeding

Start the server to automatically create the database tables:

python app.py


In a new terminal, run the seeding script to create the 5 mock contacts:

python seed.py


5. Development Server

The API will be available at: http://127.0.0.1:5000

Important Folders

/uploads: This is where the encrypted audio files (.enc) sent by the mobile app will be stored. Do not delete this folder.